Amendment No. 4 to SB2205
Yarbro
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2205* House Bill No. 2450
by adding the following new section to SECTION 1:
65-13-104. Transit project to be ADA compliant; accessibility.
(a) All stations, entrances, exits, portals, and other publicly accessible facilities
associated with a transit project must be designed and constructed in compliance with
the 2010 ADA Standards for Accessible Design adopted pursuant to § 68-120-204, and
any further amendments, supplements, or subsequent editions to such standards.
(b) An operator shall not impose additional charges for transportation to persons
with physical disabilities because of such disabilities.
(c) An operator shall ensure that each transit project provides access to vehicles
that accommodate persons with physical disabilities, including persons who use
wheelchairs or other mobility devices regardless of type.
